जो हिंदू का मुखौटा पहनकर मोदी-विरोधी, बीजेपी-विरोधी, आरएसएस-विरोधी और सनातन विरोधी अफवाहें चलाता है (कोई माहेश्वरी नहीं है)।  उनका असली नाम बदरू रशीद, पूरा नाम बदरुद्दीन रशीद लाहौरी है।   *उनका जन्म लाहौर, पाकिस्तान में हुआ था और उनकी पत्नी जूली (ईसाई लगने वाला नाम) भी पाकिस्तानी हैं, जिनका असली नाम ज़ुलेखा (स्पष्ट रूप से मुस्लिम नाम) है।*  *वे कराची में विश्व प्रसिद्ध और कुख्यात गैंगस्टर दाऊद इब्राहिम के गुप्त अलीशान बंगले में रहते हैं जहां उन्हें आईएसआई और पाकिस्तानी सेना की Y+ और Z+ सुरक्षा प्रदान की जाती है।*  *बदरू रशीद (ध्रुव राठी के रूप में फर्जीवाड़ा) की फंडिंग पाकिस्तान, चीन, दुबई, मालदीव, कनाडा, रूस, तुर्की और पेंडोरा से होती है।*  *मोदी का विरोध करने के लिए जॉर्ज सोरोस के खाते से पेसा को फंड भेजा जाता है।*  *लेकिन अब इस हिंदू विरोधी भारत विरोधी तत्व का भंडाफोड़ हो गया है*।  इस बात का खुलासा इजरायली खुफिया एजेंसी *मोसाद* ने अपनी खुफिया रिपोर्ट में किया है।   सभी *सनातनी* कृपया इस खुलासे को अधिक से अधिक शेयर करें और *बदरू रशीद*❕ की सच्चा

Do you wonder how he ( Bageshwar Maharaj )  dose that trick??? I have observed around 50 random videos in the last few hours and realized his trick - This is how it all works - before that do search the video with a title “ जब इस युवक के पर्चे ने पूरे पंडाल को हिला डाला “ 
                                             
Media Guys: PLEASE !!!!! DO READ AND TRY TO EXPOSE BY GIVING CHALLANGE OR BY KEEPING A CAMREA BEHIND HIS PAPER or Writing on an iPAD  or a Pend with a Camera that we can rewind and view with a time line!!!! ((( I bet you - Baba won't write on iPAD or with Pen provided by Media person :-))))) ) 


Step 1 ) First he writes on a Paper” generalized statements”  ; he deliberately keeps gaps in the sentence to fill it later;  gaps of one or two words
for eg: at he first writes  ---- मै दिक्कत है , ---- मैं दर्द होता है !  then he keeps the paper aside.


Step 2) Then he ask  Bhakta ( भक्त )  about his problem; if Bhakta says -
पाँव  मै problem hai  Then BABA writes these filler word in his paper (   for eg example he will write two words : say पाँव मै दिक्कत है , घुटने  मैं दर्द होता है !  etc.)  ;  IF Bhakta says सीर  mail problem hai then he will write "सीर " & "मस्तिष्क " word later to make his sentence look like > सीर मै दिक्कत है , मस्तिष्क मैं दर्द होता है ! etc. 


Step 3 Now you may say that  , we don't see him writing the filler worlds as mentioned in Step 2 ; and YES - I completely agree with you 
But this is when he writes these filler words 
if you observe it carefully then you will notice that he always write remedy or some Mantra at the end  just before handing his paper to Bhakta. And Exactly – Exactly this is the time he writes these filler words !!!!!!  ((( Don’t you wonder – IF he knows the problem and he has  written it down then why don’t he write remedy also at the same time ???? ; why he has to write it afterwords ???? )) 
4) Well, it’s also interesting to see what happens in  between;  In between -  he shows the paper to Bhakta just enough that they can read only the first few words of his sentence ; Please notice how he holds the paper and how fast he reads it loud. have studied this part very carefully for hundred’s of videos and surprising found that  99.9999% Bhakta won't read the full paper or all his writing as he is saying it loud ) ; They simply starts nodding their head ….. 


Anyways : अपने देश मै आंध भक्तोंकी कोइ कमी नहीं है। I know that after reading above 99% people won't agree with me! and that is absolutely fine. ( if 1% agree then that will change the world )

from the Bhagavad Gita, specifically Chapter 11, Verse 32. In this verse, Lord Krishna reveals His universal form to Arjuna and says:

"कालोऽस्मि लोकक्षयकृत् प्रवृद्धो लोकान्समाहर्तुमिह प्रवृत्त:।"
"I am Time, the great destroyer of the world, and I have come here to destroy all people. With the exception of you [the Pandavas], all the soldiers here on both sides will be slain."

This verse illustrates Krishna's role in the grand cosmic order and the inevitability of the destruction that is part of His divine plan. It signifies that the outcome of events, particularly in the context of the Kurukshetra War, is predetermined and unstoppable, even by Krishna Himself.
